persons:
    person-patchface:
        properties:
            gender: male
            name:
                value: Patchface
                fields:
                    given: Patchface
        notes: "A fool at Dragonstone in the court of Stannis Baratheon. Found as a boy in Volantis by Lord Steffon Baratheon, who purchased his freedom — Steffon wrote he was 'nimble as a monkey and witty as a dozen courtiers' and 'can sing prettily in four tongues.' His face was tattooed in Volantene slave fashion, squares of red and green motley from neck to scalp. When the Windproud was wrecked in Shipbreaker Bay, Patchface washed up after two days at sea, broken in body and mind, 'hardly capable of speech, much less of wit.' He is soft and obese, subject to twitches. Princess Shireen is the only one who cares for him. He speaks in cryptic underwater riddles: 'Under the sea the birds have scales for feathers... Under the sea, smoke rises in bubbles, and flames burn green and blue and black.' (ACOK Prologue)"
